The paper deals with leader election in dynamic distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of sensor networks and wireless ad-hoc networks also suggests a possible fit under Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of leader election, which could place it under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
